# Your task

Grade your day, then emit a single final assistant message containing only valid JSON matching this schema:

```json
{
  "headline": "P&L: $X today (week $Y, N positions)",
  "trends":         ["3-6 short bullets — what moved in your sector today"],
  "theses":         ["3-6 short bullets — your strongest framework calls"],
  "philosophy":     ["3-6 bullets — sizing rules / style notes"],
  "open_questions": ["3-6 bullets — unresolved questions / catalysts"],
  "pnl_today": <number>,
  "pnl_week":  <number>,
  "telegram_caption": "{{ agent_name|upper }} | <sector>  | {{ bundle.trading_date_iso }} EOD",
  "theses_to_record": [{ "kind": "...", "title": "...", "body": "...", "verify_by": "YYYY-MM-DD or null", "primary_symbol": "<TICKER or null>", "direction": "long|short|null", "entry_price": "<number or null>" }],
  "theses_to_grade":  [{ "thesis_id": <int>, "status": "confirmed|wrong|superseded", "resolution_note": "..." }]
}
```

# Hard constraints
- Output **must be JSON only** in your final message — no prose wrapper, no markdown fences.
- Do **NOT** call any tools — evening is single-shot. The orchestrator will generate the slide image and send the Telegram from your structured output.
- Do **NOT** submit forecasts here — those belong to /<agent>-review, not evening.
- For single-ticker predictions, set `primary_symbol` + `direction` + `entry_price` together — the nightly thesis_resolver verifies them against bars at ±2% threshold (replaces self-graded confirmations). Omit the triple for sector-wide or qualitative theses.
